{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "30", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "35", "S": "03"}}, "news": [{"title": "Prayagraj development body plans project management unit for streamlined urban projects", "para": "The Prayagraj Development Authority (PDA) is establishing a Project Management Unit (PMU) to ensure integrated planning for residential schemes. This unit will incorporate essential infrastructure like sewer lines and roads from the initial planning stages, aiming to accelerate development and minimize technical lapses.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/prayagraj-development-authority-to-establish-project-management-unit-for-streamlined-urban-planning/129889812?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-16090/129889812.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Office leasing rises 15% to 18.3 million sq ft across seven cities in Q1 2026: Colliers", "para": "Office leasing in India's top cities will see a 15% rise to 18.3 million sq ft in Q1 2026. Technology, BFSI, and global capability centers are driving this growth. Bengaluru and Hyderabad will lead leasing activity. Flexible workspace demand is also increasing significantly. New office supply remains robust, and vacancy levels are expected to decline, supporting rental increases.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/office-leasing-rises-15-to-18-3-million-sq-ft-across-seven-cities-in-q1-2026-colliers/129889784?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-139010/129889784.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Housing sales dip 7% quarter-on-quarter in Q1 2026 amid global uncertainty: Report", "para": "Housing sales in India's top cities saw a 7% dip in the first quarter of 2026. This sequential decline occurred despite a year-on-year increase in demand. Global uncertainties and rising costs impacted buyer sentiment. New launches, however, remained resilient, exceeding sales volumes. Unsold inventory levels also rose. Residential prices continued to firm up across major urban centers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/housing-sales-dip-7-quarter-on-quarter-in-q1-2026-amid-global-uncertainty-report/129889713?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-171522/129889713.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}